  trigger = "user 'all go' directive вҖ” cycle_032 deferred-work registry D4 (log-append automation) recommended-order #1"
  scope <<~EOF
    Build tool/atlas_cycle_append.hexa (hexa-native CLI, ~300 lines) + smoke test test/atlas_cycle_append_smoke.hexa (~120 lines, 19 checks). Design decision per cycle_032 D4 registry note: hexa-tool form (NOT git-hook) вҖ” "wilson g_verify_hexa_cli_only мҷҖ мқјкҙҖ" + .git/hooks лҠ” shared infra лқј м•Ҳм „м„ұ вҶ“. CLI лҠ” explicit invocation + reviewable. Tool reads structured cycle-draft.md (Title + 5 required sections trigger/scope/files/verifier_run_result/governance_check + optional note), validates them, scans atlas/MAIN.log.tape for max cycle_NNN, computes next, emits a tape v1.2 @A entry following cycle_032 idiom (heredoc for multi-line, quoted-string for single-line), appends via read_file_safe + concat + write_file_safe. Dry-run mode prints to stdout, skips write. This very entry is the first self-dogfood invocation вҖ” cycle_034 announces the tool itself.
  EOF
  files <<~EOF
    tool/atlas_cycle_append.hexa
    test/atlas_cycle_append_smoke.hexa
    atlas/MAIN.log.tape (this cycle entry, via the tool itself вҖ” append-only)
  EOF
  verifier_run_result <<~EOF
    atlas_cycle_append smoke: PASS (19/19 checks вҖ” pure fmt, validator, cycle-number scan, heredoc emit, dry-run path)
    atlas-verify smoke: PASS (118/118 verdicts hold + ledger live=118 vs declared=118 consistent) вҖ” re-run post-append in step 6 to confirm cycle_034 append did not break ledger consistency
  EOF
  governance_check <<~EOF
    g_arch_vs_log_split вҖ” вң… append-only respected; tool NEVER mutates existing entries (read_file_safe вҶ’ concat вҶ’ write_file_safe, no in-place edit of cycle_001..cycle_033)
    g5 hexa-native-only   вҖ” вң… pure hexa, no LLVM / no C-transpile architecture; the only exec call is `date +%Y-%m-%d` for default timestamp (overridable via --date) вҖ” same idiom as tool/atlas_cli.hexa::_now_ms
    g_self_verify         вҖ” вң… tool's correctness verified by test/atlas_cycle_append_smoke.hexa + this very dogfood invocation (the tool is its own first user)
    g_tier_default_insufficient вҖ” вң… no рҹ”ө claim attached; this is tooling, not a verdict
    g8 commit trailer     вҖ” pending parent agent commit
  EOF
  note = "D5 / D6 / D1 are next recommended-order entries in the deferred-work registry. D4's landing means subsequent cycles no longer need hand-written @A entries вҖ” `hexa run tool/atlas_cycle_append.hexa <draft.md>` is now the canonical path. The tool itself is a thin shell over pure formatter `build_entry_from_draft(draft_text, existing_log_text, date_str) -> [err, entry, cyc]` which the smoke test exercises directly (no fs touch)."
